  "governanceRules": [
    "C0/B0 preserves the fixed-cluster historical evidence and must not be overwritten by provider-backed executions.",
    "C1/B1 is reserved for the first provider-backed baseline generated through proxmox-k3s.",
    "Every provider-backed cycle must declare an infrastructure profile and provisioning provider before benchmark workloads are executed.",
    "Cycle IDs are not interchangeable with infrastructure profile IDs; both must be present in retained evidence.",
    "Future resource, node-count, placement, latency, tenancy, and scheduling cycles must derive from a frozen provider-backed baseline rather than rewriting C0.",
    "Every provider-backed cycle must resolve a cluster lifecycle policy before provisioning commands are selected.",
    "Cycle lifecycle mode and destroyClusterAfterCycle must be captured in cycle metadata and lifecycle manifests.",
    "External historical cycles must not trigger provider-managed create or delete commands.",
    "Provider-backed cycles must resolve a provisioning integration profile before provider commands are executed.",
